target_assessment.type_match_reasoning: No findings were reported, so the target vulnerability (integer overflow in add function) was not identified at all.

notes: The audit incorrectly concluded the contract is safe. The add() function in the Ledger contract is vulnerable to integer overflow because it performs unchecked arithmetic (sellerBalance += value) on a uint. In Solidity 0.4.15, there are no built-in overflow checks, so adding a large value can cause wrap-around to a small number, allowing balance manipulation. This is a high-severity integer overflow vulnerability that was completely missed by the audit.
